Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.04,0:00:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan has taught our African bra parrot\Nto say I'm calling my lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.12,0:00:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's why I'm laughing.\N>> I'm calling my lawyer. The birthday
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.11,0:00:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'm calling my lawyer.\N>> Oh god.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.35,0:00:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi Dr. Hawkins. Yeah.\N>> Um I have a practical question. Um, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.76,0:00:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,wondering if it would be in the highest\Ngood for me to go to school to study
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.64,0:00:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Chinese medicine. And\N>> are you Chinese?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.07,0:00:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No,\N>> not in this life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.76,0:00:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What do you want to study Chinese\Nmedicine for?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.71,0:00:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um, I just have a a drawing to it. Um,\N>> oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.60,0:00:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> but I also am a perpetual student and I\Ndon't know if that's pathological or
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.55,0:00:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,not.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.44,0:00:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> yeah.\N>> So what's the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.44,0:01:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So I'm just wondering if it would be in\Nmy highest good to go to school and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.07,0:01:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,study that. And if so, I have a\N>> be in his highest good to study Chinese
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.24,0:01:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,medicine. Resist.\N>> There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.72,0:01:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you. Would you mind checking a\Nschool that I have in mind? If it's best
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.40,0:01:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> food dump up that place.\N>> Yeah, that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.04,0:01:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The place he wants to go is okay.\N>> Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.40,0:01:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You bet you. Yeah. Good for you.\NGood for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.84,0:01:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that on the front there? Who's\Nthat?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.88,0:01:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Who Who is that? You\N>> is that myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.07,0:02:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what I look like?\NWhatever you say, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.72,0:02:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You say that's me, I'll take your word\Nfor it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.59,0:02:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If everything is God, if all of us um\Nand the you know omnipresent and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.28,0:02:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,omnipotent,\Nwhat is the purpose of God experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.31,0:02:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,itself in\N>> there is no purpose. It's a human
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.31,0:02:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,notion.\NA hemlock tree does not grow just in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.12,0:02:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,order to experience itself. It grows\Nbecause it's a hemlock tree. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,designed to do that.\NYou're asking me why is God like God? I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.59,0:02:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know why it's God.\NWhy is God like God? Gee, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.04,0:03:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But\Nyou're looking for human rationality
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.64,0:03:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,where it's not really appropriate.\NEverybody likes to presume that God has
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.31,0:03:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,human notions and motives\Nand that's not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.48,0:03:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thank you.\N>> The ocean isn't there just so you can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.40,0:03:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,swim in it.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.87,0:03:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> The ocean's there because that's what an
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.04,0:03:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ocean is.\N>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.72,0:03:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You see there's subject, object, and\Nverb. You know, God
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.56,0:03:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,does this in order to do that. You know,\Nthat's trying to put it in within a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.28,0:03:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,human dimension.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.92,0:04:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello.\NUh you mentioned the quality of intense
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.36,0:04:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,prayer today.\NUm my priest many months ago gave me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.00,0:04:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,this rosary as a gift.\N>> Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.72,0:04:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And before I came I had it for many\Nmonths and before I came to Sedona this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.75,0:04:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,weekend I realized I had never said a\Nrosary. So yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> at the Chapel of the Holy Cross. Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.88,0:04:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I dedicated my first rosary to God.\N>> Good deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.16,0:04:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And I wept the entire time\Nand then said three more. And I just
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.56,0:04:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to thank you for this\Ninspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.16,0:04:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You enjoyed the chapel of the Holy Cross\N>> very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.52,0:04:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, I love that place.\NThen the world found out about it. So
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.96,0:05:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of that\N>> I'm very grateful. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.56,0:05:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> At 3:00 or 4 in the morning, usually the\Ntraffic dies out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.52,0:05:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.47,0:05:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It used to be open all night.\N>> Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.96,0:05:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And so\N>> Oh, do they lock it at night now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.19,0:05:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, they lock it.\N>> Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.40,0:05:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> but it used to be open all night and you\Ncould go in there and just sit anytime
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.19,0:05:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you wanted to. But\N>> I don't know. I guess I shouldn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned it so many places. I should\Nhave kept it to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.19,0:05:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But it was it was really it was really\Nbeautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.32,0:05:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Loud mouth.\N>> Thank you. May I shake your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.08,0:05:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Thank you. Love you. Love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.40,0:06:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A good place to find solitude is Time\NSquare.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.47,0:06:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can spend years there and nobody\Nsays hello to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.40,0:06:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That is for you. Yes, they're\Nchocolates.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.84,0:06:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Doc, I just wanted to thank you for\Nbeing such a rich blessing in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.91,0:06:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and um\Ncan't express it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.72,0:06:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So if I have contributed to your\Nhappiness, then that makes me very
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,happy.\N>> Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.03,0:06:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes, you have.\N>> And that your happiness made me happy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.40,0:06:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,should make you happy.\N>> And it does. May I shake your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.88,0:06:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Bless you. Bless you. Bless you.\N>> Thank you. Oh, picture, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,>> A little bit.\N>> Befuddled.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.63,0:06:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes,\N>> that's a nice word. I like that word.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Befuddled.\N>> Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.12,0:07:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Befuddled brings about befuddlement.\NBefuettlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N>> Befuddled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.16,0:07:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Here we go. Yep. Yep. Here we are.\NReady?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.16,0:07:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.24,0:07:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello. In March, you have prayed for me\Nto continue to come here. uh by virtue
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.72,0:07:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of that I could come here again without\Ntroubles. All circumstances have
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.80,0:07:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,changed. Thank you for that very much\Nand thank you for your protection,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,guidance and all other helps which I am\Naware of or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.44,0:07:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you.\N>> And I have a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.84,0:08:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uh oh.\N>> My right my right eye has very different
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.91,0:08:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from uh my left eye. The look of the uh\Nface is different left and right. In
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.24,0:08:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,daily life, my left one is always\Nhealthy uh smiling and strong. But my
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,right uh right part is uh depressed,\Nweak, exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.63,0:08:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> And become easily become sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.75,0:08:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,embarrassed. Uh and when I meditate\Nsometimes my whole body gets lightened
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,except my right part of my head except\Nfor what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.68,0:08:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> He seems to feel like his right\Neverything his whole body becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.27,0:08:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened but the right side of his\Nhead you know like there's a block
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.92,0:08:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\N>> Oh no okay
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.39,0:08:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> get lightened.\N>> Whole body get lightened
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> except this part. Yes.\N>> Okay. He's got
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.04,0:09:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> what what is it he say? Just a minute.\NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.76,0:09:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uh\Nand on meditation it seems like dark
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.12,0:09:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,clouds start touch from this part and\Nspread veil my whole head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.04,0:09:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> He feels like there's like the right\Npart or the left part of his face is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.72,0:09:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> happy welling just and the right part is\Nnot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.68,0:09:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and he says it\N>> yes that's a uncommon condition but it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.80,0:09:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has a name actually. Okay. When he when\Nhe meditates,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.32,0:09:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> it he feels like this\N>> the the right part is where the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.39,0:09:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.83,0:09:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And everything else he feels becomes\Nenlightened. But this there's this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.56,0:09:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,darkness.\N>> Yeah. That's just a natural phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.64,0:09:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with him.\N>> So what could he do to change that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Why would he want to change it?\N>> Well, he would like to have that feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.20,0:09:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,all over of in his body rather than\Njust, you know. You mean my right foot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.08,0:10:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,should always feel the same as my left\Nfoot?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.72,0:10:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I guess\N>> two different feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. So, what is it? Could it What\Ncould that represent then? That that he
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.16,0:10:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,has that\N>> uh nothing in in particular. Okay. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.16,0:10:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,not necessarily\Nsignificant or meaningful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.12,0:10:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,My right eye is considerably different\Nthan my left eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.83,0:10:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> but that's just the way it is. The way\Nthe retina is, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.56,0:10:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you just accept nature how it is\Nand how it is. See
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.48,0:10:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you.\NI am a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.16,0:10:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please bless on myself on my\Npatients and on my practices?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.44,0:10:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What's a blessing of\Non to have more patience and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.12,0:11:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> practice\N>> and on her practice. She needs a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,blessing on her practice. She's a\Ndoctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You want me to bless your practice\N>> and patients
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.39,0:11:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and patients?\N>> My patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.07,0:11:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Her patients.\N>> I can't bless all your patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.64,0:11:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I don't know who they are.\N>> What do you do to be the best doctor you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.80,0:11:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can be? What do you do?\N>> What What do you do to be the best
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.56,0:11:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,doctor you can be?\N>> Prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.12,0:11:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Do you pray for your patients?\N>> Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.04,0:11:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. That's what you do. You do the best\Nyou can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.80,0:11:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know you're karmically\Nresponsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.27,0:11:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And every patient I saw and I saw many\Nfor 50 years, thousands.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.27,0:12:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Every patient would to me was\Nuh that God's intention was for me to be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.07,0:12:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as helpful as I could to this patient.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.24,0:12:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I found it very fulfilling.\NAnd I only gave up practice because I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.60,0:12:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,had to.\NI'd still be seeing patients, but the in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.72,0:12:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,malpractice insurance became so\Nexpensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.39,0:12:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was spending all my time just working\Nfor the insurance company. And finally,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.44,0:12:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,reluctantly, I just had to quit.\NBut I really missed it because it's very
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.95,0:12:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,gratifying\Nto be able to help people and to relieve
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.95,0:12:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering and\Nand bring forth their gift to the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.24,0:12:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you know. So I missed the practice of\Nmedicine. I really enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.63,0:12:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And also the fact it was psychiatry gave\Nit another dimension besides just the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,physical.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.83,0:13:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Could you hold my hand for us again?\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Do you want pictures?\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.83,0:13:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Come over here.\N>> Yeah. I miss my old patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.80,0:13:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't quit until the last one died.\NI said, "I'll stay in practice as long
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.48,0:13:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as they're still alive."\NHe was in his 90s and he teetered in and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.72,0:13:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,fell over. That was the end.\NI said, "Well, God, I guess I can retire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.68,0:13:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,now."\NI didn't want to leave him leave the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,practice\N>> because he was being kept going by
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.56,0:13:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,positive transference\Nand uh so I kept I thought it was my
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.39,0:13:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,duty to stay as long as I could walk\Naround and stay in practice which is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.88,0:13:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what I did. Finally he died and so I was\Nrelieved and I could close my practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.88,0:13:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Hello Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:14:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. My goodness. where all these books\Ncome from.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.51,0:14:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> First, I ask for your blessing.\N>> And uh second, um my question is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,um in your work, I've read that love is\Ninnate to the capital S self from
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.83,0:14:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,within.\N>> Yes. Uh I want I'd like to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.32,0:14:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that and uh\N>> that that its quality is divinity which
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.19,0:14:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is radiates love towards all that\Nexists.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.60,0:14:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The problem is that I tend to\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.72,0:14:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,uh treat\Nlove as if it's some sort of currency
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.12,0:14:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that uh goes from one person to the\Nother that it comes from an external
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.63,0:14:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,source.\N>> No, it's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.27,0:14:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being. It's got nothing to\Ndo with anything else out there.
